notes.__data: Inscribed on an ornate gold plaque is a message. The script is ornate, and blinks in various colours: "You are trespassing on the domain of **Werdna**. There is no possibility that you can get past my guardians! So sure am I of my defenses that I give you this clue:  "Contra-Dextra Avenue" PS - Trebor sux!"
One group of guardians have been defeated, but there are many more. Turn back while you can, fools!

A discreet sign on the wall reads: Lair of the evil wizard Werdna! Office hours 9am to 3pm by appointment onl 
The wizard is *in*!
ITS ALMOST TOO HOT TO BEAR!

SUDDENDLY YOU SEE A GROUP OF 3 HUMANOIDS.  ONE IS A BARBARIAN WITH A SWORD THAT GLOWS, ONE IS A SEXY FEMALE MAGE, AND THE THIRD LOOKS LIKE A HUGE OGRE!
THE BARBARIAN POINTS TO THE END OF THE CORRIDOR AND YELLS "ARIEL.. OOKLA.. THIS WAY!!" AND THEY ALL RUN OFF!
A sign on the door reads: *** Testing grounds control center *** Authorized personnel only! << Do not enter >>
A sign on the door reads: Private express service elevator! Authorized users only!
Suddenly, a loud alarm bell can be heard. Then the bells stop, and are replaced by the sounds of guardian monsters!
A sign on the door reads: "Monster Allocation Center"

In this room, there is a large desk. On it are the remains of crystal balls and other magical artifacts; all now broken. As you entered the room, a panel on the door slammed shut. Then it glowed a pale blue. No one can pry it open. Next, the door on the other side of the room glow bright orange, inviting the party to use it.

As the party enters the room, the door slams shut, glows orange and vanishes! A door appears to the right. A voice, coming from the ceiling addresses you: "Congratulations, brave adventurers! Today you have proved yourself to me and are now ready to start your quest! Years ago, my amulet was stolen by the evil wizard Werdnat.  Werdna hides in the maze somewhere below us. Find him; slay him; and return to me the amulet!

To aid you in your quest, I will give you a blue ribbon, which may be used to enter the elevator on this floor. Go now -- And may the gods guide you!"
A sign on the door reads: "Treasure repository."
METADATA NOT USED BUT KEEP THIS SQUARE!
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn around."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn left."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn left."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn around."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn right."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn right."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn left."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn right."
The floor has a mosaic reading: "Turn around."
You see a statue of a bear on a pedestal. On the wall is a sign reading "I've got a million of 'em."
Nobody in the party can break the door down
On a silvery disk stands a statue of a frog wearing a red and blue cape. The statue animates and shakes its legs while it yells "Yeah.... Yeah...
In this room is a statue of a monster with the body of a chicken and the head of a cat. The statue is made of bronze, and lies on an onyx pedestal.  There are unusual runes on a plaque thereon.
As you enter this room, a bronze smoke fills it. You feel compelled to leave immdediately!
As you enter this room, a silvery fog evelops you. Terrible demons form all around you. In terror, you flee from the room!
A placard near the ground reads: "A dungeon's dark..."
A placard near the ground reads: "When it's not lit..."
A placard near the ground reads: "Watch out, or you'll..."
A large sign on the wall reads: Area out of bounds!!!

In this room is a silver statue of a boar with horns and long fangs. On the wall by the statue is a message (partially obscured) that appeard to have been left by
passing elves. It is hardly legible. But some comments warning bout ghosts and demons can still be made out.
There is a gem encrusted statue of a hooded man here. A golden light emanates from the hood. In front of the statue is an altar, in which pungent incense is burning.
In this room is a statue of a monster with the body of a chicken and the head of a cat. The statue is made of bronze, and lies on an onyx pedestal. There are unusual runes on a plaque thereon.

A strange glow seems to emanate from this room. In the center, a smallish man in a long robe turns towards the party and shouts "Begone, strangers!" He slowly waves his hands, and chants "mapiro mahama diromat!!!"
